  "market_context": "Late July–early August 2023; analyst observes NASDAQ entering a monthly fair value gap, then identifies SMT divergence with ES (NASDAQ lower high vs ES higher high), waits for daily displacement and London session sweep before taking short at OTE targeting previous day low.",
  "key_observation": "NASDAQ made a lower high while ES made a higher high—creating an SMT divergence that signaled relative weakness in NASDAQ and supported bearish bias down to prior monthly low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the monthly chart, analyst identified NASDAQ had entered and closed respecting the consequent encroachment of a monthly fair value gap, suggesting potential downside toward the previous month's low.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to daily chart and observed SMT divergence: NASDAQ formed a lower high while ES formed a higher high, indicating a crack in correlation and bearish bias for NASDAQ.",
    "Step 3: Waited for daily market structure shift—confirmed by displacement candle closing below prior up-close candles—establishing bearish HTF bias.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to 15-minute timeframe, marked previous day low as draw-on liquidity, observed Asia range completion and equal lows sweep, then watched London session sweep its high followed by displacement lower.",
    "Step 5: After London sweep and displacement, analyst identified OTE zone within the intraday range, placed short entry with stop above London high, and targeted previous day low."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit previous day low before reacting; stop was placed on London high; P&L shown as +99.00 with 1 contract (frame f026).",
  "lessons": "Top-down alignment across monthly → daily → 15-minute timeframes, combined with SMT divergence and session-based liquidity sweeps, yields high-probability entries. OTE after displacement and liquidity run provides optimal risk-reward.",
